-- Morgan Stanley Says Mortgage Curbs Opportunity to Buy China Property Stock
-- B y   S h i y i n   C h e n
-- 2010-09-29T23:27:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/morgan-stanley-says-mortgage-curbs-opportunity-to-buy-china-property-stock.html
China’s stock market may “respond
negatively” in the short term after the government yesterday
announced further measures to cool the nation’s real estate
market, offering investors an opportunity to buy property and
other related stocks, Morgan Stanley said.  The measures announced don’t appear to have “much
substance,” excepting the requirement of a higher down-payment
ratio, according to a report by Jerry Lou and Allen Gui.  To contact the reporter on this story:
